IActivationFactory Interface

Definition

Enables classes to be activated by the Windows Runtime.

In this Article

[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Guid("00000035-0000-0000-C000-000000000046")]
public interface IActivationFactory

Methods

ActivateInstance()

Returns a new instance of the Windows Runtime class that is created by the IActivationFactory interface.

public object ActivateInstance ();
Returns
Object

The new instance of the Windows Runtime class.
